Year = {2025},
Volume = {19},
Number = {1},
Abstract = {While learning modules are not new to academic librarianship,
   student-centered, asynchronous learning modules are an innovative
   approach not commonly considered within the academic librarianship
   literature. This article discusses the development and implementation of
   visual literacy asynchronous learning modules created by two librarians
   for a cohort of first-year studio art students. In creating these
   modules, the goal was to offer studio art students visual literacy
   instruction specific to their personal interests and future careers.
   Specifically, this article discusses the module design process and how
   student-centered learning can be incorporated into modules in order to
   offer deep learning opportunities.},
